---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';

const title = 'Privacy Policy | Marion County Septic';
const description =
  'How Marion County Septic, operated by Compass Camper LLC, collects, uses, and shares the information you provide, and your privacy rights.';
const updated = 'June 2026';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <Breadcrumbs items={[{ name: 'Home', path: '/' }, { name: 'Privacy Policy', path: '/privacy/' }]} />
  <article class="container-narrow rich py-8">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <p>
      This website, {site.brandName} ({site.domain}), is operated by
      {site.entity.legalName}, an {site.entity.state}-registered marketing and lead
      generation company. This policy explains what information we collect, how we
      use it, and the choices you have. We are a marketing service, not a septic
      contractor, and we do not perform septic work.
    </p>

    <h2>Information we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Contact details you provide, such as your name, phone number, and email address.</li>
      <li>Property information you provide, such as your town or area, property or lot status, project type, timeline, and any description you submit.</li>
      <li>Technical data collected automatically, such as your IP address, device and browser information, and page-visit data through analytics.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How we use your information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To match you with a licensed local septic contractor who can fulfill your request.</li>
      <li>To follow up on your inquiry and respond to questions.</li>
      <li>To operate, maintain, and improve this website and our service.</li>
      <li>To comply with legal obligations, including records related to your consent to be contacted.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How we share your information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Licensed contractors.</strong> When you submit a request, your
        information is shared with one or more licensed local septic contractors
        who can schedule your free quote. Those contractors handle your
        information under their own practices.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Service providers.</strong> We use third-party providers to run
        the site and our service, such as hosting (Cloudflare), form processing
        (Web3Forms), analytics (Google Analytics), and, in the future, call
        tracking. They process data on our behalf.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Legal reasons.</strong> We may disclose information if required by
        law or to protect our rights, users, or the public.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not sell your personal information.</p>

    <h2>Data retention</h2>
    <p>
      We keep your information for as long as reasonably necessary for the
      purposes above. Records related to your consent to be contacted are
      typically retained for at least five years, consistent with federal
      telephone consumer protection guidance.
    </p>

    <h2>Your choices and rights</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>You may opt out of contact at any time, including by replying STOP to any text message or asking to be removed during any call.</li>
      <li>You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of your personal information.</li>
      <li>
        If you are a California resident, the CCPA and CPRA give you rights to
        know, delete, correct, and opt out of the sale or sharing of personal
        information. We do not sell personal information. To exercise any right,
        contact us using the email below.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For privacy requests or questions, email
      <a class="link-inline" href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>.
    </p>

    <p>
      This policy may be updated from time to time. Material changes will be
      reflected by the date above.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
